      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>Robert Jones Peterburg resident, collector and dealer of
         African American research materials acquired several monthly
         teaching reports for Sussex County, Virginia. The reports were
         generated by three teachers and the County Clerk.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Names of individual students, grade enrolled, number of
         students, age and textbooks used. Each report also gives the
         teacher name and home address.</p>
         <p>Grade sheets for three African American public schools in
         Sussex County, Virginia 1899.</p>
      </scopecontent>
